contains

boolean contains(int sId,
                 int pId,
                 int oId)
Answer true iff the graph contains a triple matching the triple pattern specified by the given identifiers. An identifier of -1 represents a wildcard.

Parameters:
sId - the identifier for the subject of the triple pattern
pId - the identifier for the predicate of the triple pattern
oId - the identifier for the object of the triple pattern

find

Iterator<IdBasedTriple> find(int sId,
                             int pId,
                             int oId)
Executes a triple pattern query specified by the given identifiers. An identifier of -1 represents a wildcard.

Parameters:
sId - the identifier for the subject of the triple pattern
pId - the identifier for the predicate of the triple pattern
oId - the identifier for the object of the triple pattern
